text:
This document, version 2.0 of the GM RSA procedure, was produced following:
• a review of RSA best practice;
• a review of the TfGM Road Safety Audit Procedure Version 1.0 (March 2016), and;
• an assessment from a sample of RSA reports, briefs and response reports, produced by designers and auditors working to the previous procedures to ascertain the degree of compliance.

As a guide the following information should be provided, but not limited to:
• General arrangement details;
• Location plan;
• Collision data; and
• Traffic flow data.

The details to be provided are to be agreed prior to undertaking the RSA with the Overseeing Organisation, however and as a guide, the following information should be provided, as appropriate:
• General arrangement details;
• Site clearance details;
• Traffic signs and road markings;
• Drainage alterations;
• Street lighting alterations;
• Traffic signal details and traffic signal staging alterations;
• Carriageway and footway level alterations;
• Swept path analysis, and
• Surfacing and material details/specifications.
